From Mexico City , you may take the metro to the Tasqueña station and follow the " autobuses " signs to the southern bus depot next door . The various bus companies display their destinations and times . Pullman de Morelos offers bus service every 30 minutes and a one-way ticket cost M$ 134 (
pesos
) in 2018 . The bus ride is comfortable , scenic and takes about an hour and a half ( depending on traffic ) . Upon arrival in Tepoztlan , the bus may drop you at a depot on the edge of town . Taxis will be waiting to take you to the main square for M$ 40 . Walking to the center will take 20-30 minutes or so . The path to walk downtown is marked by a red metal guard rail across from the bus station .
